Ford Go-Bike Dataset System

by ( Sara Farghaly )

Investigation Overview

Ford Go-Bike Data System were collected from LYFT app. GoBike gave opportunity to rent and ride the bicycle in San Francisco City.

Dataset Overview

The Dataset were collected for first 4-months of 2019 in daily interval dataset. the data were collected from the location that the customer was taken or rent the bike and the time were measured in hour, minute, and second. and by the end of the ride when the customer left it is bike, final destination was collected with the ended time. Additionally, the longitude and latitude of both starting and ending point were measured. The gender of the costumers was also taken into consideration were collecting the data as same as the user types for the GoBike whether they are members - subscribers- or just costumers. finally, the visualization will give deep vision of the data.

Univariate Exploration

Lets Take General Look on the Data

(Visualization 1)

Durning the first 4 months of 2019 the Males were using the GoBike more than Females and Others. it can gave idea that man would prefer to skip the traffic jam while going to the work or enjoying doing some sport by using GoBike

Conclusion

The Ford GoBike Data System gave good view especially when we took random samples. the members were higher than the customers while the shared bike were for whos the most gender were using the bike as the males were the higher, while the shared bike were very low except in April. the map showed three different location for rent, rider, and ending the trip of the bike. in respect of gender, the members who born in 1988 where the higher in using the bike. finally, the Other and Females were the more in using bikes in long distance in Kilometer.
